definition.value: Sexual arousal from a person's partner or partners not being able to see for any of various reasons or from having sex in total darkness.
Note that amaurophilia does not pertain to a fetishistic desire to be blind or to such a desire to have sex with a blind person or persons.
Sexual arousal from darkness or partial darkness; or an ability to only experience arousal in such situations.
A person who has undergone amputation, i.e. the removal of a bodily extremity, typically (but not always) as a result of surgery.
A kiss in which a person's lips contact another person's anus.
The act of touching the anus in a way that causes involuntary twitching movements or laughter.
Licking of the anus as a form of sexual arousal.
An act in which someone inserts their penis in their anus.
Any suction exerted by the mouth; response of the mammalian infant to draw milk from the breast. Includes sucking on inanimate objects.
Sucking of the finger. This is one of the most common manipulations of the body found in young children.
Sucking of the penis, especially during sexual intercourse or specifically during penile ejaculation.
Sucking of the vagina, especially during sexual intercourse.
Sucking of the anus, especially during sexual intercourse.
A sexual attraction to significantly taller or shorter people.
A sexual attraction to significantly shorter people (or preferring a shorter partner generally).
A cartoon of non-human animal or object which is given humanoid features.
Eating other individuals of one's own species.
In animals, eating other individuals of one's own species.
An instance in which a person eats another person or consumes the flesh of another person.
A situation in which a member of a species cannibalizes another prior to, or after, copulation.
Sexual arousal from cannibalism preceded by rape.
The practice of eating one's self or part of one's self.
A form of pica in which a part bites, eats, or attempts to eat parts of one's own body.

The compulsive eating of hair associated with trichotillomania (hair pulling). In trichophagia, people with trichotillomania also ingest the hair that they pull; in extreme cases this can lead to a hair ball (trichobezoar).
Co-occurring necrophilia and cannibalism.
A practice of cannibalism in one's own locality or community.
The consumption of flesh outside one's close social group—for example, eating one's enemy.
Cannibalism of the corpse of a person who is already dead.
Cannibalism of the corpse of a person after killing them, typically for food.
Feeding on corpses or carrion.
The consumption of animal flesh.
The act of eating young women or virgins.
A substance that increases sexual desire, sexual pleasure, or sexual behavior.
Chemical agents or odorants that stimulate sexual desires.
Note that many of the items appearing in this class may or may not have aphrodisiac-related effects, but are nonetheless strongly believed to be aphrodisiacs.
An aphrodisiac which is created through a natural process.
An aphrodisiac which is created through a synthetic process.
An error in consistency of the characteristics of people, plot, objects, and places seen by the reader or viewer over some period of time.

A gap or inconsistency in a storyline that goes against the flow of logic established by the story's plot. Such inconsistencies include things as illogical, unlikely or impossible events, and statements or events that contradict earlier events in the storyline.
A type of plot hole which is not realized at first because a person was so caught up in the story, characters, and events of a particular story.
A type of fridge logic which becomes terrifying given the realization of said fridge logc.
A legal gender (or gender marker) that appears on any of various identity documents.
A legal gender (or gender marker) that appears on a driver's license.
A legal gender (or gender marker) that appears on a passport.
A legal gender (or gender marker) that appears on a birth certificate.
A legal gender (or gender marker) that appears on a death certificate.

An administrative gender (or gender marker) that is registered with an insurance provider of some kind.
An administrative gender (or gender marker) that is registered with a health insurance provider.
An administrative gender (or gender marker) that is registered with a vehicle insurance provider.
An action taken over the course of or as the result of a legal process.

An official proclamation by a judge (or panel of judges) that defines the legal relationships between the parties to a hearing, a trial, an appeal or other court proceedings. Such ruling requires or authorizes the carrying out of certain steps by one or more parties to a case. A court order must be signed by a judge; some jurisdictions may also require it to be notarized.
A court order which states that an individual's legal name should be changed.
